<br>
What you'd need to do, Arist, is figure out a time/day of the week when most of our far-flung membership could make it, and start PLUGGING it both here and in game.  It helps to schedule it far enough in advance so people can make plans to attend.<br>
<br>
Getting together has always been one of our problems, primarily because this guild from its inception has included international members, so we have had varying time zones including all of the continental US, Australia, and places in Europe (at the moment the other zones include Japan, Egypt, and Norway I believe).<br>
<br>
We are also due to the nature of the guild hampered somewhat by the fact that many of our members are irregular or infrequent players.  It makes it nice for them to have a place to come to/belong to and familiar faces whenever they do drop in to play, but much harder for those who do play regularly to schedule large events.<br>
<br>
